component industry telecommunications predecessor racal millicom  to  founded   years ago  headquarters london head office newbury berkshire england registered office area served worldwide key people gerard kleisterlee chairman vittorio colao ceo products fixed line telephone mobile phone broadband digital television internet television iptv revenue £ billion  operating income £ billion  profit £ billion  total assets £ billion  total equity £ billion  number of employees   divisions vodafone global enterprise subsidiaries list vodacom group vodafone albania vodafone australia vodafone czech republic vodafone egypt vodafone faroe islands vodafone germany vodafone ghana vodafone greece vodafone hungary vodafone iceland vodafone india vodafone ireland vodafone italy vodafone malta vodafone netherlands vodafone new zealand vodafone portugal vodafone romania vodafone spain vodafone turkey vodafone qatar vodafone uk vodafone ukraine website vodafonecom vodafone group plc ˈvoʊdəfoʊn is a british multinational telecommunications company with headquarters in london it predominantly operates services in the regions of asia africa europe and oceania among mobile operator groups globally vodafone ranked fifth by revenue and second behind china mobile in the number of connections  million as of update vodafone owns and operates networks in  countries and has partner networks in over  additional countries its vodafone global enterprise division provides telecommunications and it services to corporate clients in  countries vodafone has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it had a market capitalisation of approximately £ billion as of  february update the eighthlargest of any company listed on the london stock exchange it has a secondary listing on nasdaq contents  name  history  evolution as a racal telecom brand  to   vodafone group then vodafone airtouch plc  to   vodafone group plc  to present  adverts  operations  africa and the middle east  the americas  asiapacific  europe  vodafone global enterprise  products and services  mobile money transfer services  mhealth services  vodafone foundation  corporate affairs  senior management  financial results  criticisms  tax avoidance  communications blackout during the arab spring  poor customer service  unlimited roaming costs on stolen phones  breaches of consumer protection rules  surveillance infrastructure  references  external links nameedit the name vodafone comes from voice data fone the latter a sensational spelling of phone chosen by the company to reflect the provision of voice and data services over mobile phones historyedit the evolution of vodafone started in  with the establishment of the racal strategic radio ltd subsidiary of racal electronics the uks largest maker of military radio technology which formed a joint venture with millicom called racal which evolved into the present day vodafone evolution as a racal telecom brand  to edit vodafones original logo used from  to  in  sir ernest harrison obe the then chairman of racal electronics agreed to a deal with lord weinstock of the general electric company to allow racal to access some of gecs tactical battle field radio technology the head of racals military radio division gerry whent was briefed by ernest harrison to drive the company into commercial mobile radio whent visited a mobile radio factory run by general electric unrelated to gec in virginia usa the same year to understand the commercial use of military radio technology jan stenbeck head of a growing swedish conglomerate set up an american company millicom inc and approached racals whent in july  about bidding jointly for the uks second cellular radio licence the two struck a deal giving racal  of the new company racalmillicom ltd and millicom  due to uk concerns about foreign ownership the terms were revised and in december  the racalmilicom partnership was awarded the second uk mobile phone network license final ownership of racalmillicom ltd was  racal with millicom holding  plus royalties and venture firm hambros technology trust holding  according to the uk secretary of state for industry the bid submitted by racalmillicom ltd… provided the best prospect for early national coverage by cellular radio vodafone was launched on  january  under the new name racalvodafone holdings ltd with its first office based in the courtyard in newbury berkshire and shortly thereafter racal strategic radio was renamed racal telecommunications group limited on  december  racal electronics issued shares to the minority shareholders of vodafone worth gb£ million and vodafone became a fully owned brand of racal on  october  racal telecom majority held by racal electronics went public on the london stock exchange with  of its stock floated the successful flotation led to a situation where racals stake in racal telecom was valued more than the whole of racal electronics under stock market pressure to realise full value for shareholders racal demerged racal telecom in  vodafone group then vodafone airtouch plc  to edit on  september  racal telecom was demerged from racal electronics as vodafone group with gerry whent as its ceo in july  vodafone acquired the twothirds of talkland it did not already own for £ million on  november  in a defensive move vodafone purchased peoples phone for £ million a  store chain whose customers were overwhelmingly using vodafones network in a similar move the company acquired the  of astec communications that it did not own a service provider with  stores in january  gerald whent retired and christopher gent took over as the ceo the same year vodafone introduced its speechmark logo composed of a quotation mark in a circle with the os in the vodafone logotype representing opening and closing quotation marks and suggesting conversation on  june  vodafone completed its purchase of airtouch communications inc and changed its name to vodafone airtouch plc the merged company commenced trading on  june  to gain antitrust approval for the merger vodafone sold its  stake in eplus mobilfunk the acquisition gave vodafone a  share of mannesmann owner of the largest german mobile network on  september  vodafone agreed to merge its us wireless assets with those of bell atlantic corp to form verizon wireless the merger was completed on  april  just a few months prior to bell atlantics merger with gte to form verizon communications inc in november  vodafone made an unsolicited bid for mannesmann which was rejected vodafones interest in mannesmann had been increased by the latter purchase of orange the uk mobile operator chris gent would later say mannesmanns move into the uk broke a gentlemans agreement not to compete in each others home territory the hostile takeover provoked strong protest in germany and a titanic struggle which saw mannesmann resist vodafones efforts however on  february  the mannesmann board agreed to an increased offer of £ billion then the largest corporate merger ever the eu approved the merger in april  when vodafone agreed to divest the orange brand which was acquired in may  by france télécom vodafone group plc  to presentedit the headquarters of vodafone romania in bucharest on  july  the company reverted to its former name vodafone group plc in  the company acquired eircell the largest wireless communications company in ireland from eircom eircell was subsequently rebranded as vodafone ireland vodafone then went on to acquire japans thirdlargest mobile operator jphone which had introduced camera phones first in japan on  december  vodafone introduced the concept of partner networks by signing tdc mobil of denmark the new concept involved the introduction of vodafone international services to the local market without the need of investment by vodafone the concept would be used to extend the vodafone brand and services into markets where it does not have stakes in local operators vodafone services would be marketed under the dualbrand scheme where the vodafone brand is added at the end of the local brand ie tdc mobilvodafone etc in  vodafone entered into a title sponsorship deal with the mclaren formula one team which traded as vodafone mclaren mercedes until the sponsorship ended at the end of the  season in may  vodafone group plc bought the remaining shares of vodafone essar from essar group ltd for  billion on  december  it acquired the reading based bluefish communications ltd – an ict consultancy company the acquired operations formed the nucleus of a new unified communications and collaboration practice within its subsidiary – vodafone global enterprise which will focus on implementing strategies and solutions in cloud computing and strengthen its professional services offering in april  vodafone announced an agreement to acquire cable  wireless worldwide cww for £ billion vodafone was advised by ubs ag while barclays and rothschild advised cable  wireless the acquisition will give vodafone access to cwws fibre network for businesses enabling it to take unified communications solutions to large enterprises in uk and globally and expand its enterprise service offerings in emerging markets on  june  cable  wireless shareholders voted in favour of the vodafone offer exceeding the  of shares necessary for the deal to go ahead on  june  vodafone announced it would be buying german cable company kabel deutschland the takeover is valued at € billion and was recommended over the bid of rival liberty global on  september  vodafone announced it would be selling its  stake in verizon wireless to verizon communications for us billion in one of the biggest deals in corporate history in october  vodafone began its rollout of g to provincial new zealand with the launch of the system in holiday hotspots around coromandel in february  vodafone made an offer to acquire spains largest cable operator ono in a deal rumoured to be around € billion advertsedit since  the adverts feature two bees named jack and mike other adverts feature star wars character yoda idris elba does voice over for adverts in  the new slogan live life on g was launched operationsedit africa and the middle eastedit networks in the middle east and africa majorityowned minorityowned partner networks dr congo egypt kenya kuwait ghana lesotho bahrain mozambique qatar libya tanzania south africa uae majority stakes held through majorityowned vodacom group effective ownership is not majority but full control exercised by the group egypt in november  the vodafone egypt network went live under the name clickgsm on  november  the company announced a deal with telecom egypt resulting in further cooperation in the egyptian market and increasing its stake in vodafone egypt after the deal vodafone egypt was  owned by the group while the remaining  was owned by telecom egypt on  january  vodafone complied with egyptian government instructions to suspend internet service in selected areas during a period of antimubarak protests the company issued a statement that under egyptian legislation the authorities have the right to issue such an order and we are obliged to comply with it vodafone also received public and media criticism for allowing the authorities to send mass progovernment messages via sms over their network during the protests one such message requested that honest and loyal men should confront the traitors and criminals vodafone later issued a statement asserting that they had no choice but to allow the messages to be broadcast and that they had complained to the egyptian authorities about the practice kuwait on  september  vodafone signed a partner network agreement with mtc group of kuwait the agreement involved the rebranding of mtc to mtcvodafone on  december  vodafone signed another partner network agreement with kuwaits mtc group the second agreement involved cooperation in bahrain and the branding of the network as mtcvodafone south africa vodacom on  november  the company announced that its south african affiliate vodacom had agreed to introduce vodafones international services such as vodafone live and partner agreements to its local market in november  vodafone announced that it was in exclusive talks to buy a  stake of venfin in vodacom group reaching agreement the following day vodafone and telkom then had a  stake each in vodacom vodafone now owns  of vodacom after purchasing a  stake from telkom on  october  the company offered to acquire an additional  per cent stake in vodacom group from telkom the finalised details of the agreement were announced on  november  the agreement called for telkom to sell  per cent of its  per cent stake in vodacom to the group and demerge the other  per cent to its shareholder meanwhile vodafone has agreed to make vodacom its exclusive subsaharan africa investment vehicle as well as continuing to maintain the visibility of the vodacom brand the transaction closed in mayjune  on  may  vodacom entered the jse limited stock exchange in south africa after vodafone increased its stake by  to  to take a majority holding despite disputes by local trade unions in april  vodacom rebranded with the vodafone logo qatar in december  a vodafone groupled consortium was awarded the second mobile phone licence in qatar under the name vodafone qatar vodafone qatar is located at qstp the qatar science  technology park commercial operations officially began on  march  ghana on  july  vodafone agreed to acquire a  stake in ghana telecom for  million the acquisition was consummated on  august  the same groupled consortium won the second fixedline licence in qatar on  september  on  april  ghana telecom along with its mobile subsidiary onetouch was rebranded as vodafone ghana uae on  january  the group announced a partner network agreement with du the secondlargest operator in the united arab emirates the agreement involved cooperation on international clients handset procurement mobile broadband etc libya on  february  the group signed a partner network agreement with the secondlargest operator in libya al madar cameroon on  september  vodafone extended its activities to cameroon by signing a partnership with afrimax a glte telecommunications operator in africa vodafone cameroon launched a youth program in the universities to support and encourage the cameroonian students the americasedit chile on  may  vodafone sealed a trade agreement with the chilean entel pcs chile in which entel pcs has access to the equipment and international services of vodafone and vodafone will be one of the trademarks of entel for the wireless business this step will give the vodafone brand access to a market of over  million people currently divided among two companies telefonica movistar and entel pcs brazil in august  vodafone has started the mvno operation in brazil as a corporative mm operator united states in the united states vodafone previously owned  of verizon wireless in a joint venture with verizon communications the countrys largest mobile carrier vodafone branding was not used however as the cdma network was not compatible with the gsm  mhz standard used by vodafones other networks and as vodafone did not have management control over verizon wireless on  september  vodafone announced the sale of its stake to verizon communications for around  billion in  vodafone made an unsuccessful bid for the entirety of att wireless however cingular wireless at the time a joint venture of sbc communications and bellsouth both now part of att inc ultimately outbid vodafone and took control of att wireless the combined wireless carrier is now att mobility in  vodafone was considered for acquisition by us based att ultimately the deal did not move forward in december  vodafone announced an agreement with tmobile us to launch a mobile virtual network operator mvno service using its network set to launch in  asiapacificedit networks in asiapacific majorityowned partner networks australia afghanistan arm