ics firm listed on the london stock exchange and once a constituent of the ftse  index racal was a diversified company offering products including voice loggers and data recorders point of sale terminals laboratory instruments military electronics including radio and radar at its height it operated throughout  countries worldwide and employed over  people it was the parent company of vodafone before the mobile telephony provider was sold in  racal was purchased by thomsoncsf now thales group in  thereby giving the french firm access to the lucrative uk defence and armaments market contents  foundation  racal under harrison  major deals  decca radar  vodafone  chubb security  racal telecoms  racal instrumentation  national lottery  breakup  references  external links foundationedit racal was created in  as racal ltd the name being derived from the partners raymond brown and george calder cunningham ernest harrison joined the company as employee number  as an accountant but later held the positions of chief buyer personnel director and contract negotiator the first factory was located in isleworth west london on outgrowing this site it moved to bracknell berkshire in  enticed by a year lease at four shillings and sixpence per square foot  and no rent reviews although racal had won a royal navy contract to build and supply a variant of the american collins model j radio receiver they were not granted a licence to build these sets by collins inc this meant that racal had to design and build a radio receiver from scratch after almost bankrupting the company due to a £ overspend the result was the ra  in production from  to at least   designed in cooperation with trevor wadley and utilising his wadley loop circuit racal under harrisonedit harrison joined the company board in  and as deputy managing director from  helped racal to obtain a stock market listing harrison became chairman in  when cofounder ray brown was lured away by the ministry of defence major dealsedit  negotiation of a british army battlefield radio contract initially larkspur later part of clansman which secured the future of racal led the merger between racal and british communications corporation that bolstered racal’s radio business bought decca in  in competition from general electric company plc the rival british company led by lord weinstock buying the british rail telecommunications network to form the basis of racal telecom creation and spinout of vodafone stopping the proposed takeover by williams holdings by demerging chubb investing in national lottery company camelot group selling racal telecom to global crossing selling racals remaining defence and industrial electronics divisions to thomsoncsf of france for £ billion under harrsion £ invested in racal in  would have been worth £million when he retired in  harrison received an estimated £ million from the sale of racal in  and is estimated to have died with an accumulated total wealth of £million decca radaredit in  racal bought decca radar forming racaldecca racaldatacom conducted business in the united states vodafoneedit main article vodafone in  harrison agreed a deal with lord weinstock of general electric company plc to allow racal to access some of gecs tactical battlefield radio technology briefing the head of racals military radio division gerry whent to drive the company into commercial mobile radio whent visited ges factory in virginia usa in  in  racals newly formed subsidiary racal strategic radio ltd under ceo whent won one of two uk cellular telephone network licences the other going to british telecom the network known as racal vodafone was  owned by racal with millicom with  and the hambros technology trust  respectively vodafone was launched on january   racal strategic radio was renamed racal telecommunications group limited in  on december   racal electronics bought out the minority shareholders of vodafone for gb£ million in   of racal telecom was floated on the london stock exchange this would lead to the situation where racal electronics was valued at less than its shareholding in racal telecom harrison demerged racal telecom in october  forcing a positive valuation on the rest of racal colloquially known in the city of london as the rump vodafone would later become the largest mobile network in the world and the highest valued company on the ftse  immediately following the demerger williams holdings launched a takeover bid for racal the bid valued at £m failed chubb securityedit in  racal bought chubb a security company that manufactured safes and locks in  chubb was demerged from racal and was subsequently taken over by willams holdings in  for £bn racal telecomsedit racal reestablished a telecoms division with a major government contract in  and the acquisition of british rail telecommunications in  this division of the former nationalised industry owned telecoms infrastructure laid across the rail network racal instrumentationedit consisted of racal recorders hythe southampton and racal instruments burham near slough racal acquired thermionic products in  creating racal thermionics renamed racal recorders in  national lotteryedit main article camelot group in  camelot group won the franchise to operate the uk national lottery racal had a  share after one of the founder shareholders gtech was bought out by camelot this stake increased to  which thales continues to hold breakupedit in  racal expanded its defence businesses with the acquisition of the thorn sensors group from thorn emi in  all of racal defence businesses were reorganised under racal defence electronics ltd into racal radar defence systems racal radio and racal thorn in october  racal decided to sell its telecoms business to the american communications group global crossing for £bn then in january  thomsoncsf announced a bid for the company racal became thomsoncsf racal plc and later part of thales plc with the renaming of the larger thomsoncsf to thales group in december  racal acoustics ltd was acquired by esterline technologies and has become part of their communications systems platform referencesedit  ra  archived from the original on june     a b sir ernest harrison daily telegraph february   archived from the original on november   retrieved june     a b c d sir ernest harrison chairman of racal electronics london daily telegraph february   retrieved june     brewerton david february   sir ernest harrison london the guardian archived from the original on march   retrieved june     a b jim levi britains high priest of shareholder value salbucoza archived from the original on july   retrieved june     the wadley drift cancelling loop archived from the original on december     sperry marine archived from the original on february     richard wilson february   obituary sir ernest harrison electronicsweeklycom archived from the original on september   retrieved june     a profile of world leader vodafone november   archived from the original on september   retrieved april     a b vodafone group public ltd co archived from the original on april   retrieved april     the rapid rise of vodafone bbc news february   archived from the original on april   retrieved may     eadie alison december   racal pays £ million to own vodafone the times times newspapers  accessdate requires url help  upwardly mobile racal and vodafone the economist   how high a price can racal bring new york times  archived december   at the wayback machine  camelot wins uk lottery race bbc news may   archived october   at the wayback machine  racal buys thorn emi sensors janes   racal sells telecoms division bbc news october   accessed january   archived february   at the wayback machine  thomsoncsf seals racal deal bbc news january   accessed january   archived april   at the wayback machine external linksedit thales group website thales uk website v t e thales group divisions and subsidiaries thales air defence thales australia thales communications thales navigati