untries vodafone has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it had a market capitalisation of approximately £ billion as of  february update the eighthlargest of any company listed on the london stock exchange it has a secondary listing on nasdaq contents  name  history  evolution as a racal telecom brand  to   vodafone group then vodafone airtouch plc  to   vodafone group plc  to present  adverts  operations  africa and the middle east  the americas  asiapacific  europe  vodafone global enterprise  products and services  mobile money transfer services  mhealth services  vodafone foundation  corporate affairs  senior management  financial results  criticisms  tax avoidance  communications blackout during the arab spring  poor customer service  unlimited roaming costs on stolen phones  breaches of consumer protection rules  surveillance infrastructure  references  external links nameedit the name vodafone comes from voice data fone the latter a sensational spelling of phone chosen by the company to reflect the provision of voice and data services over mobile phones historyedit the evolution of vodafone started in  with the establishment of the racal strategic radio ltd subsidiary of racal electronics the uks largest maker of military radio technology which formed a joint venture with millicom called racal which evolved into the present day vodafone evolution as a racal telecom brand  to edit vodafones original logo used from  to  in  sir ernest harrison obe the then chairman of racal electronics agreed to a deal with lord weinstock of the general electric company to allow racal to access some of gecs tactical battle field radio technology the head of racals military radio division gerry whent was briefed by ernest harrison to drive the company into commercial mobile radio whent visited a mobile radio factory run by general electric unrelated to gec in virginia usa the same year to understand the commercial use of military radio technology jan stenbeck head of a growing swedish conglomerate set up an american company millicom inc and approached racals whent in july  about bidding jointly for the uks second cellular radio licence the two struck a deal giving racal  of the new company racalmillicom ltd and millicom  due to uk concerns about foreign ownership the terms were revised and in december  the racalmilicom partnership was awarded the second uk mobile phone network license final ownership of racalmillicom ltd was  racal with millicom holding  plus royalties and venture firm hambros technology trust holding  according to the uk secretary of state for industry the bid submitted by racalmillicom ltd… provided the best prospect for early national coverage by cellular radio vodafone was launched on  january  under the new name racalvodafone holdings ltd with its first office based in the courtyard in newbury berkshire and shortly thereafter racal strategic radio was renamed racal telecommunications group limited on  december  racal electronics issued shares to the minority shareholders of vodafone worth gb£ million and vodafone became a fully owned brand of racal on  october  racal telecom majority held by racal electronics went public on the london stock exchange with  of its stock floated the successful flotation led to a situation where racals stake in racal telecom was valued more than the whole of racal electronics under stock market pressure to realise full value for shareholders racal demerged racal telecom in  vodafone group then vodafone airtouch plc  to edit on  september  racal telecom was demerged from racal electronics as vodafone group with gerry whent as its ceo in july  vodafone acquired the twothirds of talkland it did not already own for £ million on  november  in a defensive move vodafone purchased peoples phone for £ million a  store chain whose customers were overwhelmingly using vodafones network in a similar move the company acquired the  of astec communications that it did not own a service provider with  stores in january  gerald whent retired and christopher gent took over as the ceo the same year vodafone introduced its speechmark logo composed of a quotation mark in a circle with the os in the vodafone logotype representing opening and closing quotation marks and suggesting conversation on  june  vodafone completed its purchase of airtouch communications inc and changed its name to vodafone airtouch plc the merged company commenced trading on  june  to gain antitrust approval for the merger vodafone sold its  stake in eplus mobilfunk the acquisition gave vodafone a  share of mannesmann owner of the largest german mobile network on  september  vodafone agreed to merge its us wireless assets with those of bell atlantic corp to form verizon wireless the merger was completed on  april  just a few months prior to bell atlantics merger with gte to form verizon communications inc in november  vodafone made an unsolicited bid for mannesmann which was rejected vodafones interest in mannesmann had been increased by the latter purchase of orange the uk mobile operator chris gent would later say mannesmanns move into the uk broke a gentlemans agreement not to compete in each others home territory the hostile takeover provoked strong protest in germany and a titanic struggle which saw mannesmann resist vodafones efforts however on  february  the mannesmann board agreed to an increased offer of £ billion then the largest corporate merger ever the eu approved the merger in april  when vodafone agreed to divest the orange brand which was acquired in may  by france télécom vodafone group plc  to presentedit the headquarters of vodafone romania in bucharest on  july  the company reverted to its former name vodafone group plc in  the company acquired eircell the largest wireless communications company in ireland from eircom eircell was subsequently rebranded as vodafone ireland vodafone then went on to acquire japans thirdlargest mobile operator jphone which had introduced camera phones first in japan on  december  vodafone introduced the concept of partner networks by signing tdc mobil of denmark the new concept involved the introduction of vodafone international services to the local market without the need of investment by vodafone the concept would be used to extend the vodafone brand and services into markets where it does not have stakes in local operators vodafone services would be marketed under the dualbrand scheme where the vodafone brand is added at the end of the local brand ie tdc mobilvodafone etc in  vodafone entered into a title sponsorship deal with the mclaren formula one team which traded as vodafone mclaren mercedes until the sponsorship ended at the end of the  season in may  vodafone group plc bought the remaining shares of vodafone essar from essar group ltd for  billion on  december  it acquired the reading based bluefish communications ltd – an ict consultancy company the acquired operations formed the nucleus of a new unified communications and collaboration practice within its subsidiary – vodafone global enterprise which will focus on implementing strategies and solutions in cloud computing and strengthen its professional services offering in april  vodafone announced an agreement to acquire cable  wireless worldwide cww for £ billion vodafone was advised by ubs ag while barclays and rothschild advised cable  wireless the acquisition will give vodafone access to cwws fibre network for businesses enabling it to take unified communications solutions to large enterprises in uk and globally and expand its enterprise service offerings in emerging markets on  june  cable  wireless shareholders voted in favour of the vodafone offer exceeding the  of shares necessary for the deal to go ahead on  june  vodafone announced it would be buying german cable company kabel deutschland the takeover is valued at € billion and was recommended over the bid of rival liberty global on  september  vodafone announced it would be selling its  stake in verizon wireless to verizon communications for us billion in one of the biggest deals in corporate history in october  vodafone began its rollout of g to provincial new zealand with the launch of the system in holiday hotspots around coromandel in february  vodafone made an offer to acquire spains largest cable operator ono in a deal rumoured to be around € billion advertsedit since  the adverts feature two bees named jack and mike other adverts feature star wars character yoda idris elba does voice over for adverts in  the new slogan live life on g was launched operationsedit africa and the middle eastedit networks in the middle east and africa majorityowned minorityowned partner networks dr congo egypt kenya kuwait ghana lesotho bahrain mozambique qatar libya tanzania south africa uae majority stakes held through majorityowned vodacom group effective ownership is not majority but full control exercised by the group egypt in november  the vodafone egypt network went live under the name clickgsm on  november  the company announced a deal with telecom egypt resulting in further cooperation in the egyptian market and increasing its stake in vodafone egypt after the deal vodafone egypt was  owned by the group while the remaining  was owned by telecom egypt on  january  vodafone complied with egyptian government instructions to suspend internet service in selected areas during a period of antimubarak protests the company issued a statement that under egyptian legislation the authorities have the right to issue such an order and we are obliged to comply with it vodafone also received public and media criticism for allowing the authorities to send mass progovernment messages via sms over their network during the protests one such message requested that honest and loyal men should confront the traitors and criminals vodafone later issued a statement asserting that they had no choice but to allow the messages to be broadcast and that they had complained to the egyptian authorities about the practice kuwait on  september  vodafone signed a partner network agreement with mtc group of kuwait the agreement involved the rebranding of mtc to mtcvodafone on  december  vodafone signed another partner network agreement with kuwaits mtc group the second agreement involved cooperation in bahrain and the branding of the network as mtcvodafone south africa vodacom on  november  the company announced that its south african affiliate vodacom had agreed to introduce vodafones international services such as vodafone live and partner agreements to its local market in november  vodafone announced that it was in exclusive talks to buy a  stake of venfin in vodacom group reaching agreement the following day vodafone and telkom then had a  stake each in vodacom vodafone now owns  of vodacom after purchasing a  stake from telkom on  october  the company offered to acquire an additional  per cent stake in vodacom group from telkom the finalised details of the agreement were announced on  november  the agreement called for telkom to sell  per cent of its  per cent stake in vodacom to the group and demerge the other  per cent to its shareholder meanwhile vodafone has agreed to make vodacom its exclusive subsaharan africa investment vehicle as well as continuing to maintain the visibility of the vodacom brand the transaction closed in mayjune  on  may  vodacom entered the jse limited stock exchange in south africa after vodafone increased its stake by  to  to take a majority holding despite disputes by local trade unions in april  vodacom rebranded with the vodafone logo qatar in december  a vodafone groupled consortium was awarded the second mobile phone licence in qatar under the name vodafone qatar vodafone qatar is located at qstp the qatar science  technology park commercial operations officially began on  march  ghana on  july  vodafone agreed to acquire a  stake in ghana telecom for  million the acquisition was consummated on  august  the same groupled consortium won the second fixedline licence in qatar on  september  on  april  ghana telecom along with its mobile subsidiary onetouch was rebranded as vodafone ghana uae on  january  the group announced a partner network agreement with du the secondlargest operator in the united arab emirates the agreement involved cooperation on international clients handset procurement mobile broadband etc libya on  february  the group signed a partner network agreement with the secondlargest operator in libya al madar cameroon on  september  vodafone extended its activities to cameroon by signing a partnership with afrimax a glte telecommunications operator in africa vodafone cameroon launched a youth program in the universities to support and encourage the cameroonian students the americasedit chile on  may  vodafone sealed a trade agreement with the chilean entel pcs chile in which entel pcs has access to the equipment and international services of vodafone and vodafone will be one of the trademarks of entel for the wireless business this step will give the vodafone brand access to a market of over  million people currently divided among two companies telefonica movistar and entel pcs brazil in august  vodafone has started the mvno operation in brazil as a corporative mm operator united states in the united states vodafone previously owned  of verizon wireless in a joint venture with verizon communications the countrys largest mobile carrier vodafone branding was not used however as the cdma network was not compatible with the gsm  mhz standard used by vodafones other networks and as vodafone did not have management control over verizon wireless on  september  vodafone announced the sale of its stake to verizon communications for around  billion in  vodafone made an unsuccessful bid for the entirety of att wireless however cingular wireless at the time a joint venture of sbc communications and bellsouth both now part of att inc ultimately outbid vodafone and took control of att wireless the combined wireless carrier is now att mobility in  vodafone was considered for acquisition by us based att ultimately the deal did not move forward in december  vodafone announced an agreement with tmobile us to launch a mobile virtual network operator mvno service using its network set to launch in  asiapacificedit networks in asiapacific majorityowned partner networks australia afghanistan armenia india azerbaijan fiji new zealand malaysia samoa singapore sri lanka taiwan thailand turkmenistan uzbekistan vietnam vodafone shop at nadi airport fiji in july  bellsouth new zealands network went live and october  vodafone australias network also went live this was followed in july  by vodafone fijis network going live in november  vodafone purchased bellsouth new zealand which later became vodafone new zealand in  jphone launched the jsky mobile internet service in response to docomos imode service in december  jphones g network went live on  october  jphone became vodafone japan and jphones mobile internet service jsky became vodafone live in march  vodafone sold vodafone japan to softbank in october  softbank changed vodafone japans name to softbank mobile on  november  singapore became a part of the community as m was signed as partner network in december  vodafone australia agreed to deploy highspeed mpls backbone network built by lucent worldwide services using juniper hardware then in april  smartone changed the name of its brand to smartonevodafone after both companies signed a partner network agreement in august  vodafone launched g technology in new zealand and in october  it began launching g technology in australia on  october  the company announced the acquisition of a  per cent stake in indias bharti enterprises which operates the largest mobile phone network in india under the brand name airtel the headquarters of vodafone new zealand in auckland city in january  indonesia malaysia and sri lanka were added to the vodafone footprint as vodafone group signed a partner network agreement with telekom malaysia on  march  vodafone announced an agreement to sell all its interest in vodafone japan to softbank for £ billion of which £ billion will be received in cash on closing of deal vodafone japan later changed its name to softbank mobile in november  vodafone divested its remaining softbank shares on  october  vodafone new zealand bought new zealands rd largest internet service provider ihug on  february  along with the partnership with digicel caribbean see below samoa was added as a partner market then on  february  the company agreed to acquire a controlling interest of  in hutch essar for us billion at the same time it agreed to sell back  of its airtel stake back to the mittals vodafone would retain a  stake in airtel on  september  hutch was rebranded to vodafone in india on  february  vodafone group signed a threeyear partnership agreement with digicel group the agreement which includes digicels sister operation in samoa will result to the offering of new roaming capabilities the two groups will also become preferred roaming partners of each other on  february  vodafone announced the launching of mpaisa mobile money transfer service on roshans afghanistans largest gsm operator network afghanistan was added to the vodafone footprint on  september  vodafone purchased australias largest bricks and mortar mobile phone retailer crazy johns adding  retail stores to its local operations on  february  vodafone australia announced a merger with hutchison via a joint venture company vha pty ltd which would offer products under the vodafone brand dtac in thailand is signed as a partner network of the group on  march  on  june  vodafonehutchison australia vha announced the end of its outsourcing of retail operations vha committed to buying back and managing its entire retail operation including  vodafonebranded retail outlets australiawide this project was slated to be completed by  september  on  august  vha enabled an extended  mhz g umts network which functions outside their  mhz g network boosting vodafones g population coverage from around  to around  on dualband  mhz g umts devices nar mobile in azerbaijan was signed as a partner network on  july  while chunghwa telecom of taiwan was signed on  november  in february  vodafone together with china mobile participated in bidding for one of the two newly opened myanmar mobile licences in october  it was reported by reuters that vodafone planned to invest as much as  billion £ billion to buy out minority shareholders in vodafone india in july  vodafone sold its  shareholding of vodafone fiji to the fiji national provident fund under the terms of the deal vodafone fiji retained its branding under a partner market agreement at the beginning of september  vinaphone signed a strategic cooperation agreement with vodafone by late january  vodafone group plcs unit in india and idea cellular ltd were in preliminary talks to merge and on  march  vodafone announced that it was merging its indian business with idea indias thirdlargest network to create the countrys largest operator  with almost  million customers accounting for  of the indian cellphone service market vodafone would own  percent of the new operator and ideas parent company the aditya birla group would own  percent the deal valued vodafone india at the equivalent of  billion and idea cellular at the equivalent of  billion the deal would enable vodafone to move its indian subsidiary off its balance sheet cutting the british group’s net debt by the equivalent of almost  billion europeedit networks in europe majorityowned partner networks albania austria belgium czech republic bulgaria channel islands germany croatia cyprus greece denmark estonia hungary finland faroe islands ireland iceland latvia italy lithuania luxembourg malta macedonia norway netherlands russia serbia north cyprus slovenia sweden portugal switzerland ukraine romania spain turkey uk vodafone hungary was formed as a subsidiary company in july  in february  radiolinja of finland joined as a partner network and later changed its named to elisa later that year the company rebranded japans jsky mobile internet service as vodafone live and in december  the vodafone brand was introduced in the estonian market following the signing of a partner network agreement with radiolinja eesti which later changed its name to elisa in january  the company signed a groupwide partner agreement with mobilkom austria and as a result austria bulgaria croatia and slovenia were added to the community in april  og vodafone was introduced in the icelandic market and in may  omnitel omnitel prontoitalia was rebranded vodafone italy on  july  lithuania was added to the community with the signing of a partner network agreement with bitė in february  vodafone signed a partner network agreement with luxembourgs luxgsm and a partner network agreement with cyta of cyprus cyta agreed to rename its mobile phone operations to cytamobilevodafone in april  the company purchased a british airtime provider singlepoint for £m from john caudwells caudwell group adding approximately  million customers and sites in stokeontrent to existing sites in newbury hq birmingham warrington and banbury in november  vodafone introduced g services into europe in june  the company bought the czech mobile operator oskar on  july  oskar of the czech republic was rebranded as oskarvodafone on  october  connex in romania was rebranded as connexvodafone and on  october  the company reached an agreement to sell vodafone sweden to telenor for approximately € billion after the sale vodafone sweden became a partner network in december  vodafone won an auction to buy turkeys secondlargest mobile phone company telsim for us billion in  the company rebranded its stokeontrent site as stoke premier centre a centre of expertise for the company dealing with customer care for its higher value customers technical support sales and credit control on  february  the company announced that it was extending its footprint to bulgaria with the signing of partner network agreement with mobiltel which is part of the mobilkom austria group the headquarters of vodafone ireland in dublin in april  the company announced that it had signed an extension to its partner network agreement with bite group enabling its latvian subsidiary bite latvija to become the latest member of vodafones global partner community on  may  vodafone announced the thenbiggest loss in british corporate history £ billion and plans to cut  jobs it reported oneoff costs of £ billion due to the revaluation of its mannesmann subsidiary on  july  the respected head of vodafone europe bill morrow quit unexpectedly and on  august  the company announced the sale of its  stake in belgiums proximus for € billion after the deal proximus was still part of the community as a partner network on  october  vodafone announced the first single brand partnership with og vodafone which would operate under the name vodafone iceland and on  december  the company announced the sale of its  stake in switzerlands swisscom for chf billion £ billion after the deal swisscom would still be part of the community as a partner network finally in december  the company completed the acquisition of aspective an enterprise applications systems integrator in the uk signalling vodafones intent to grow a significant presence and revenues in the information and communication technologies ict marketplace the vodafone lion on the löwenparade in munich germany early in january  telsim in turkey adopted vodafone dual branding as telsim vodafone and on  april  telsim vodafone turkey dropped its original brand and became vodafone turkey in addition vodafone turkey also gives service in northern cyprus on  may  vodafone added jersey and guernsey to the community as airtel was signed as partner network in both crown dependencies in june  the vodafone live mobile internet portal in the uk was relaunched front page was now charged for and previously bundled data allowance was removed from existing contract terms all users were given access to the full web rather than a walled garden and vodafone became the first mobile network to focus an entire media campaign on its newly launched mobile internet portal in the uk on  august  vodafone portugal launched vodafone messenger a service with windows live messenger and yahoo messenger at the end of  vodafone germany was ranked th in europe by subscriber numbers whilst its italian operation was listed as th vodafone uk was ranked th whilst spain was listed in th place on  april  vodafone extended its footprint to serbia as vip mobile was added to the community as a partner network and on  may  the company added vip operator as a partner network thereby extending the global footprint to the republic of macedonia on  october  the company announced a strategic nonequity partnership with mobile telesystems mts group of russia the agreement adds russia armenia turkmenistan ukraine and uzbekistan to the group footprint on  march  it was announced that the groups luxembourg partner has been changed to tango the agreement with luxgsm was not renewed in favour of tango the luxembourg unit of another partner network belgacom of belgium on  april  vodafone sold its  stake in sfr the second largest operator in france to vivendi for € billion in march  the spanish operations of vodafone signed an agreement with orange sa to coinvest € billion in the expansion of spains fibreoptic cable broadband network this will enable vodafone to reach an additional  million customers in spain by  in october  russias mobile telesystems and vodafone expanded their  strategic partnership this resulted in the rebranding of mts ukraine to vodafone ukraine on  december  vodafone groups dutch operations merged with liberty globals ziggo brand creating vodafoneziggo group holding bv vodafone global enterpriseedit main article vodafone global enterprise a map showing the countries where vodafone global enterprise has operations coloured in red vodafone global enterprise is the business services division and a wholly owned subsidiary of vodafone group it was established in april  to provide telecommunications and information technology services to large corporations the division offers integrated communication solutions in cloud computing unified communications and collaboration its services include domestic and international voice and data machinetomachine services mobile email mobile broadband managed services mobile payment and mobile recording in december  it acquired the readingbased bluefish communications ltd an ict consultancy company the acquired operations formed the nucleus of a new unified communications and collaboration practice within vge working on cloud computing and professional services vodafone global enterprise operates in over  countries with northern europe based in london united kingdom central europe southern europe and africa asia pacific  subsaharan africa based in singapore and americas geographical divisions vges major customers include deutsche post the linde group unilever and volkswagen group products and servicesedit a vodafone shop selling a range of products in leeds england in october  it launched vodafone  a new internet service for the mobile pc and mac this was discontinued in december  after disappointing hardware sales this was after the director of internet services resigned in september  tweeting  days before i leave vodafone freedom beckons in february  vodafone launched the worlds cheapest mobile phone known as vodafone  intended to sell for below  £ in the developing world it was initially launched in india turkey and eight african countries including lesotho kenya and ghana mobile money transfer servicesedit in march  safaricom which is part owned by vodafone and the leading mobile communication provider in kenya launched a mobile payment solution developed by vodafone by february  the mpesa money transfer system in kenya had gained  million customers by  there were fourteen million mpesa accounts by which held  percent of the countrys savings following mpesas success in kenya vodafone announced that it was to extend the service to afghanistan the service here was launched on the roshan network under the brand mpaisa with a different focus to the kenyan service mpaisa was targeted as a vehicle for microfinance institutions mfi loan disbursements and repayments alongside businesstobusiness applications such as salary disbursement the afghanistan launch was followed in april  by the announcement of further a further launch of mpesa in tanzania south africa and india in february  vodafone announced a worldwide partnership with visa mhealth servicesedit in november  vodafone announced the creation of a new business unit focused on the emerging mhealth market the application of mobile communications and network technologies to healthcare one of its early success stories is with the novartisled sms for life project in tanzania for which vodafone developed and deployed a textmessage based system that enables all of the countrys  public health facilities to report their levels of antimalarial medications so that stock level data can be viewed centrally in realtime enabling timely resupply of stock during the sms for life pilot which covered  health facilities over six months stockouts dropped from  to  saving thousands of lives vodafone foundationedit the vodafone foundation is a recognised charity which supports and initiates projects which use mobile technology to benefit the vulnerable using the slogan connecting for good they often work in collaboration with other charitable groups below are some examples of their initiatives tecsos – mobile phones have been adapted to allow victims of domestic violence to activate immediate contact with the emergency services if they are in danger paediatric epilepsy remote monitoring system – a monitoring system that allows physicians to remotely make patient observations safe taxi system – an initiative in portugal that consists of technology that taxi drivers can use to alert police if they are in danger of being assaulted learning with vodafone solution – technology that allows teachers in india to use graphical and multimedia content to enhance their teaching the world of difference programme – successful applicants choose charities for which they work either fulltime for two months or parttime for four months minimum  hours a week the charities are provided with £ with each winner receiving the balance as a salary after ni and tax have been paid corporate affairsedit part of the vodafone campus in newbury berkshire vodafones registered address and uk headquarters and its world headquarters until  senior managementedit sir gerald whent at that time an executive with racal electronics plc was responsible for the bid for a uk cellular network licence the mobile telecoms division was demerged and was floated on the london stock exchange in october  and sir gerald became chief executive of racal telecom plc over the next few years the company grew to become the uks market leader changing its name to vodafone group plc in the process sir christopher gent took over as chief executive in january  after sir geralds retirement gent was responsible for transforming vodafone from a small uk operator into the global operator through the merger with the american airtouch and the takeover of germanys mannesmann arun sarin was the driving force behind the companys move into emerging markets such as asia and africa through the purchases such as that of turkish operator telsim and a majority stake in hutchison essar in india the fourth ceo vittorio colao stepped up from deputy chief executive in july  chief executive tenure sir gerald whent october  – december  sir christopher gent january  – july  arun sarin july  – july  vittorio colao since july  financial resultsedit vodafone reports its results in accordance with international financial reporting standards ifrs financial performance has been as follows year ended  march turnover £m profit before tax £m profit for the year £m basic eps pence proportionate customers m                                                                                     losses for year to  march  reflect write downs of assets principally in relation to the mannesmann acquisition proportionate turnover includes £ million from discontinued operations criticismsedit uk uncut protestors outside a vodafone shop in liverpool tax avoidanceedit in september  an investigation by private eye magazine revealed certain details of vodafones tax avoidance activities it was reported that vodafone routed the acquisition of mannesmann through a luxembourg subsidiary set up to avoid paying tax on the deal and continued to place its profits in luxembourg following a long legal struggle with hmrc during which a senior hmrc official john connors switched sides to become head of tax at vodafone it was eventually agreed that vodafone would pay £ billion related to the acquisition based on vodafones accounts experts have estimated the potential tax bill written off as a result of the negotiations was over £ billion the news of this legal tax avoidance sparked angry protests beginning in october  and ongoing as of april  outside vodafone shops across the uk organised under the banner of uk uncut the first protests caused the simultaneous closure of over a dozen stores including the flagship oxford street branch in  private eye magazine and the bureau of investigative journalism alleged that vodafones swiss branches were run by a single parttime bookkeeper the report claimed hardly any business was done from there indicating that the main purpose of the zug office was tax avoidance the report claimed the money was borrowed from the swiss branch of the luxembourg company allowing it to take advantage of luxembourgs laws which exempts foreign branches of companies from tax and swiss laws which almost completely exempt local branches of foreign companies according to the expose this would have otherwise generated a british tax bill on a little over £ billion it said vodafone publishes a single combined set of accounts for its luxembourg subsidiaries and their swiss branches for the one company profits worth £ billion were taxed at less than  in  and the profits are likely to have been attributed to switzerland in its response to these allegations vodafone has said the swiss branch has not been involved in vodafones global financing for a number of years it is therefore irrelevant in respect to global financing arrangements vodafone was also assessed a us billion tax over its acquisition of hutchison whampoas indian assets in  a demand that it contests in january  the highest indian court ruled that vodafone is not liable for taxes and penalties of up to £ billion however in february  indias tax department sent vodafone a renewed tax notice of £bn following the siding of the indian court with vodafone in  the government changed the law to allow firms to be retrospectively taxed communications blackout during the arab springedit vodafone was implicated in the violent suppression of prodemocracy protests in egypts  demonstrations on  january vodafone responsible for much of egypts telecommunication infrastructure shut off all voice and data services for egyptian citizens and businesses at the request of the egyptian government under hosni mubarak the daily telegraph of the uk reported the egyptian governments action is unprecedented in the history of the internet usbased internet intelligence firm renesys stated in an action unprecedented in internet history the egyptian government appears to have ordered service providers to shut down all international connections to the internet vodafone group ceo vittorio colao said the company was obliged by law to comply with the instructions of the egyptian government at the companys annual general meeting on  june the campaign groups access and fairpensions asked vodafone to endorse a plan to prevent the company facing similar demands in the future poor customer serviceedit in australia particularly towards the end of  vodafone have been heavily criticised due to allegations of poor customer service and severe technical inadequacies which earned them their nickname vodafail – a website of the same name still exists in response they have developed a new network and now provide a day satisfaction guarantee unlimited roaming costs on stolen phonesedit vodafone uk in common with other operators has been criticised for holding customers on regular monthly billed contracts liable for almost unlimited roaming costs when their phones are stolen abroad despite being seemingly able to limit costs of payasyougo contracts breaches of consumer protection rulesedit in october  vodafone was fined a record £m by ofcom for serious breaches of consumer protection rules in april  vodafone continued to have major issues with customer service with the ceo nick jeffery inviting customers with unresolved complaints to email him directly surveillance infrastructureedit in june  vodafone revealed information about theirs and other telecommunication operators direct access systems content data and metadata interception programmes globally referencesedit  a b c d e f g annual report  pdf vodafone group plc retrieved  april    vodafone moves world hq to london bbc news  june  retrieved  january    gsma intelligence  september  gsma intelligence – research – operator group ranking q  gsmaintelligencecom retrieved  june   vodafone is ranked second by connections and fifth by revenue    where we are vodafone group plc retrieved  january    vodafone global enterprise vodafone group plc retrieved  january    ftse allshare index ranking stockchallengecouk retrieved  june 